<para>  <image type="html" name="surface-mesh-topology-logo.png"></image>
   Guillaume Damiand and Francis Lazarus This package provides a toolbox for manipulating curves on a combinatorial surface from the topological point of view. Two main functionalities are proposed. One is the computation of shortest curves that cannot be continuously deformed to a point. This includes the computation of the so-called edge width and face width of the vertex-edge graph of a combinatorial surface. The other functionality is the homotopy test for deciding if two given curves on a combinatorial surface can be continuously deformed one into the other.    <bold>Introduced in:</bold> CGAL 5.1<linebreak/>
